#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:3
msgid "Multi-tiered bitlevel systems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:5
msgid "RhostMUSH offers a multi-tier bitlevel system.  They go in order of presidence You do not have to use all these bits, only use what you want."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:9
msgid "ghod (#1) <bitlevel 7>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:11
msgid "This bitlevel can do everything.  Only those who you trust with absolute power should have this.  Period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:15
msgid "Immortal <bitlevel 6>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:17
msgid "The only thing this bitlevel can not do is directly effect #1, set/unset some internal flags/attributes, and set/unset the immortal flag.  These players can do EVERYTHING else.  Treat this bit as you would treat #1.  Only give it to those you know without a doubt you can trust."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:22
msgid "Can do everything except set some internal flags, effect #1, and set/remove the immortal flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:26
msgid "Royalty <bitlevel 5>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:28
msgid "This is your standard wizard.  They can do everything you're used to on other mushes that wizards can do.  In addition, they also override all locks by default (this can be disabled), and they have an enhanced wizcloaking ability (which also can be disabled).  They can also set all the lower bitlevels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:33
msgid "All things of Level 4 and lower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:34
msgid "Ability to set more flags: STOP, NOSTOP, FUBAR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:35
msgid "Ability to @attribute,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:36
msgid "Ability to WIZCLOAK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:39
msgid "Councilor <bitlevel 4>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:41
msgid "This is your almost-but-not-quite wizard.  They have access to about 80% of the wizard commands.  This includes @nuke, @toad, @newpassword and the like.  The only things they can't do that wizards can is cloak, override locks, and use some of the database manipulation tools in wizhelp."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:46
msgid "All things of Level 3 and lower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:47
msgid "Ability to set more flags: NOCONNECT, WANDERER, FREE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:49
msgid "Ability to @nuke, @toad, @boot, @chownall, @dbck, @poor,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:49
msgid "@newpassword, @pcreate, slay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:52
msgid "Architect <bitlevel 3>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:54
msgid "This is your sub-wizard.  They still have the ability to control anything their bitlevel and lower (including @chown, @destroy, etc) but do not have any control of other players (like @nuke, @toad, etc) but they can set the slave flag.  Otherwise, all things their level and lower they can treat as if they owned it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:59
msgid "All things of Level 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:60
msgid "Ability to fully control and modify anything their level and lower (including @cloning, @destroying, etc)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:62
msgid "Ability to use @tel on anything their level and lower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:63
msgid "Ability to bypass jump_ok rooms on anything their level & lower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:64
msgid "Ability to set some restricted flags: SLAVE, NO_YELL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:65
msgid "Has infinite quota and money"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:66
msgid "Able to give negative money (Steal)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:67
msgid "Able to @toggle the MONITOR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:70
msgid "Guildmaster <bitlevel 2>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:72
msgid "This is the lowest wiz bit.  They only have moderate abilities. They can examine/decompile anything their level and lower, they can @guild/@quota people, and they have a few other minor abilities. They don't have free money however."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:76
msgid "Ability to access things remotely (long_fingers)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:77
msgid "Things are FREE for them in the queue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:78
msgid "Can see dbref#'s of things their level and lower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:79
msgid "Can examine/decompile things their level and lower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:80
msgid "Can set @quota/@guild on their level and lower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:83
msgid "Wanderer <bitlevel 0>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:85
msgid "This is a hinderance flag.  This flag is automatically set on new players that are created (which can be disabled).  This flag stops the player from creating/destroying any database information.   In effect it stops them from any type of building type commands.  They still are allowed to set/unset locks/attributes/etc though without hinderance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:93
msgid "Guest <bitlevel 0 as well>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:95
msgid "This is a bigger hinderance flag.  By default all guests should be set this.  This flag stops the player from ANY database manipulation along with @teleporting, and many other advanced commands.  It's extreamly dehibilatating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:102
msgid "Altering bitlevels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/15-bitlevels.rst:104
msgid "Please keep in mind each of these bitlevels can be tweeked with the @admin parameters and with the @powers (accessable by royalty) or @depowers (only by immortal and higher)."
msgstr ""
